results.name: Decimal expansion of 2*sqrt(3)/(3*Pi).
comment: The ratio of the volume of a cube to the volume of the circumscribed sphere (which has circumradius a*sqrt(3)/2 = a*A010527, where a is the cube's edge length; see MathWorld link). For similar ratios for other Platonic solids, see A165922, A049541, A165953, and A165954. A063723 shows the order of these by size.
results.author: _Rick L. Shepherd_, Oct 02 2009
